159
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,292
克劳斯喜欢把我们装进棺材
Klaus gets his jollies
from keeping us in a box,

160
00:08:21,467 --> 00:08:23,992
直到他决定把匕首拔出来
until he decides to
pull the dagger out.

161
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,161
他一定是这么对付以利亚的
That must be what
he's done to Elijah.

162
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,307
这个是我的
This one's mine.

163
00:08:29,475 --> 00:08:32,035
他随时准备着你的棺材
He keeps your coffin on standby.

164
00:08:32,211 --> 00:08:34,509
他喜欢做好准备
以防他的家人
He likes to be prepared
for when his family members,

165
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:36,477
让他失望
inevitably, disappoint him.

166
00:08:36,649 --> 00:08:39,209
以利亚的棺材不在这里
他一定把他藏在别处了
Elijah's isn't here.
He must have stashed him elsewhere.

167
00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:41,413
我感觉好恶心
I feel sick.

168
00:08:41,587 --> 00:08:42,986
欢迎加入真祖家族，亲爱的
Welcome to the family, love.

169
00:08:43,155 --> 00:08:45,680
你一发现以利亚不见就该逃走的
You should have run, the second
you realized Elijah was gone.

170
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:48,952
是啊，但女巫在我身上下咒了
Yeah, well, the witches have
put some sort of hex on me.

171
00:08:49,128 --> 00:08:51,619
只要我怀着这个孩子
就不能离开纽奥良
As long as I'm carrying this baby,
I can't leave New Orleans.

172
00:08:51,797 --> 00:08:53,059
一旦这么做，她们会杀了我
If I do, they kill me.

173
00:08:53,232 --> 00:08:55,029
我了解克劳斯，一旦你生下肚子里
Knowing Klaus,
he's planning a box for you,

174
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:57,692
那个不知什么的东西
他就会替你准备棺材了
the second you give birth to
whatever's cooking in your tum.

175
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:01,302
我一我到以利亚就走
I'm leaving,
as soon as I find Elijah.

176
00:09:01,474 --> 00:09:04,466
数十年插着匕首躺在棺材里糟糕透了
Being daggered in a
box for decades sucks.

177
00:09:06,112 --> 00:09:07,511
相信我
Trust me.

178
00:09:08,481 --> 00:09:10,676
你最好想办法破除咒语逃走
You best find a way
to break that hex and run.

179
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:35,373
有人吗？
Hello?

180
00:09:36,709 --> 00:09:38,301
不是吧，马赛尔
Seriously, Marcel?

181
00:09:38,477 --> 00:09:39,842
想吓唬我吗？
Trying to scare me?

182
00:09:40,012 --> 00:09:42,913
昨晚你的人被杀跟我毫无关系
I had nothing to do with
the attack on your guys last night!

183
00:10:00,566 --> 00:10:01,624
苏菲德弗罗
Sophie Deveraux.

184
00:10:01,801 --> 00:10:03,996
我哥哥以利亚跟我提过你
My brother, Elijah,
told me about you.

185
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:05,694
知道我是谁吗？
Know who I am?

186
00:10:05,871 --> 00:10:07,839
嗯，知道
Yeah, I know.

187
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:09,941
那你知道我们该好好谈谈了
Then, you know I need to talk.

188
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:12,703
要我猜的话，根据克劳斯过去的作为
So, if I had to guess,
knowing Klaus' history,

189
00:10:12,878 --> 00:10:15,142
以利亚现在胸口插着匕首
Elijah has a dagger in his chest.

190
00:10:15,314 --> 00:10:17,680
那是个魔法物
你是女巫
It's a magical object.
You're a witch.

191
00:10:17,850 --> 00:10:20,478
施个定位咒
找到匕首就能找到以利亚
Do a locator spell,
locate the dagger, locate Elijah.

192
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:24,047
我不能使用魔法
这是死罪
I can't use magic.
It's punishable by death.

193
00:10:24,223 --> 00:10:26,453
- 马赛尔的规矩
- 马赛尔？
-Marcel's rules.
-Marcel?

194
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:28,218
你觉得如果你不能给我我想要的
What do you think
I'm going to do to you,

195
00:10:28,394 --> 00:10:29,691
我会对你做什么呢？
if you don't give me what I want?

196
00:10:29,862 --> 00:10:31,090
做不了什么
Not much.

197
00:10:32,064 --> 00:10:33,395
我被连结了
I've been linked.

198
00:10:33,566 --> 00:10:35,966
你对我做什么
就是对海莉做什么
So, anything you do to me,
you do to Hayley.

199
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,432
谁？
Who?

200
00:10:37,603 --> 00:10:39,833
对了，怀孕的那个
Oh, right, the mumsy.

201
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:42,236
算你走运，以利亚似乎很在乎她
Well, luckily for you,
Elijah seems to care about her.

202
00:10:42,408 --> 00:10:44,239
否则我现在就扭断你的脖子
Otherwise, I'd break your neck,
right here.

203
00:10:47,546 --> 00:10:49,741
马赛尔怎么会有这么大能耐？
How did Marcel get
so bloody powerful, anyway?

204
00:10:49,915 --> 00:10:52,008
我一百年前离开时可不是这样的
He wasn't like this when I left
a hundred years ago.

205
00:10:52,385 --> 00:10:55,183
马赛尔有办法知道
有人在法语区使用魔法
Marcel has a way to tell whenever
there's magic done in the Quarter.

206
00:10:55,354 --> 00:10:56,343
他是怎么做到的并不重要
The how isn't relevant.

207
00:10:56,522 --> 00:10:58,251
我告诉你什么不重要
I'll tell you
what's not bloody relevant.

208
00:10:58,424 --> 00:11:00,358
一群不能使用魔法的女巫
A coven of witches
who can't do magic.

209
00:11:00,526 --> 00:11:02,426
我的主意是，搬走吧
Here's an idea, move away.

210
00:11:02,595 --> 00:11:04,688
我们习得的是祖传魔法
We practice ancestral magic.

211
00:11:04,864 --> 00:11:08,265
这片墓地都是我们祖先的遗体
This cemetery is filled with
the remains of our witch ancestors.

212
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:11,301
不能接近他们，我们就没有能力
Without access to them,
we're powerless.

213
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:14,439
如果我们逃走
我们就抛弃了遗赠
If we run,
we're leaving our legacy behind.

214
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:16,040
我们的家、我们的家人
Our home, our family.

215
00:11:18,577 --> 00:11:20,272
家人可没那么重要
Well, family's overrated.

216
00:11:25,384 --> 00:11:30,788
看看我
我回到一个只带给我心痛的城市
Look at me, I'm back in a city
that's given me nothing but heartache,

217
00:11:30,956 --> 00:11:33,754
寻找下决心保护一个孩子的哥哥
Iooking for a brother
who's hell-bent on protecting a baby

218
00:11:33,926 --> 00:11:34,915
我根本不在乎那孩子
I don't care about.

219
00:11:35,094 --> 00:11:36,527
很难相信
I find that hard to believe.

220
00:11:37,596 --> 00:11:39,894
- 你还是来了
- 我是为以利亚而来
-You're here, aren't you?
-I'm here for Elijah.

221
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:42,398
一找到他，我立刻走
The instant I find him, I'm gone.

222
00:11:42,568 --> 00:11:45,036
他傻乎乎地相信
He was the one who
idiotically believed this baby

223
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:47,365
这个孩子会是尼克劳斯的救赎
would be Niklaus' redemption.

224
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,475
而现在他失踪了，大概是克劳斯所为
And now, he's missing,
probably at the hands of Klaus himself.

225
00:11:52,778 --> 00:11:55,542
而你傻得可以，居然相信
以利亚可以说服克劳斯
You were foolish enough to believe
that Elijah could convince Klaus

226
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:58,513
对付马赛尔
大家都知道他俩的过去
to go against Marcel, when everyone
knows that they have a history.

227
00:11:58,684 --> 00:12:01,050
- 我知道克劳斯和马赛尔是父子关系
- 你不懂
-Klaus sired Marcel, I'm aware.
-You don't understand.

228
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:04,417
马赛尔不是随便什么
克劳斯转变成吸血鬼的人
Marcel is not just some guy
that Klaus turned into a vampire.

229
00:12:05,958 --> 00:12:07,289
克劳斯把他当儿子一样疼爱
Klaus loved him like a son.

230
00:12:08,828 --> 00:12:11,058
他们相遇的那天我也在
REBEKAH:
I was there the day that they met.

231
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:14,131
我们去埋葬艾米尔，州长的独子
We were burying Emil,
the governor's only son.

232
00:12:16,102 --> 00:12:17,160
我们是这么以为的
Or so we thought.

233
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,368
结果发现州长还有一个儿子
It turns out,
the governor had another son,

234
00:12:20,539 --> 00:12:22,063
是和他的一个奴隶所生
from a mother that he owned.

235
00:12:45,464 --> 00:12:46,692
你叫什么名字？
What is your name?

236
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:51,393
我没有名字
Don't got one.

237
00:12:51,570 --> 00:12:54,971
妈妈想要等到我十岁才给我取名
她怕我会死于热病
Mama wouldn't name me, 'til l
turned ten. Case the fever took me.

238
00:12:55,975 --> 00:12:57,135
结果她却得热病死了
Then it took her.

239
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,404
你是个幸存者
You're a survivor.

240
00:13:02,882 --> 00:13:05,282
幸存者需要名字
And survivors need names.

241
00:13:08,254 --> 00:13:09,983
马赛勒斯怎么样？
How 'bout Marcellus?

242
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:12,355
马赛勒斯？
Marcellus?

243
00:13:12,525 --> 00:13:15,983
来自于玛尔斯，战争之神
It comes from Mars, the god of war.

244
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:21,825
意思是“小战士”
And it means, "little warrior".

245
00:13:32,945 --> 00:13:35,641
看来我们的兄弟还是有救的
Perhaps there is hope
for our brother, after all.

246
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:38,943
克劳斯在那个男孩身上看到了自己
Klaus saw himself in the boy.

247
00:13:39,118 --> 00:13:41,916
他想起了我们父亲以前是怎么打他的
He remembered how our
father used to beat him.

248
00:13:42,087 --> 00:13:44,885
他也是个私生子，而父亲就当他
He, too, was the bastard child
of a man who saw him as nothing

249
00:13:45,057 --> 00:13:46,547
是头畜生
but a beast.

250
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:55,592
这就是为什么你的计划不会成功
And that is why your plan will fail.

251
00:13:55,768 --> 00:13:58,931
你所做的只是把两个
迷失已久的灵魂凑在一起
All you've done is bring back together
two long-lost souls.

252
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:03,198
没有了以利亚
谁知道他们会做出什么事来？
Without Elijah between them,
who knows what they'll do?

253
00:14:12,785 --> 00:14:15,515
这可比昨晚的派对差远了
Well, this is a far cry
from last night's party.

254
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:26,025
原来是想追卢梭酒吧的酒保啊
In pursuit of the bartender
from Rousseau's, I see.

255
00:14:26,832 --> 00:14:28,197
正在努力
She's a work in progress.

256
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:30,198
你坐在这里为她消得人憔悴
And yet, here you are,
pining over her,

257
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:32,894
而没有拿她当午餐
when you should be
eating her for lunch.

258
00:14:33,072 --> 00:14:35,131
她一定很特别
Well, she must be special.

259
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,843
先谈正事，验尸官打电话来了
Business, first.
The coroner called.

260
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:40,376
他有我的电话
万一出现进客的尸体就联系我
He's got my number,
in case any dead tourists show up.

261
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:43,140
让我精猜，手上盖着印记
Let me guess.
Dead tourists with a stamp on their hand

262
00:14:43,315 --> 00:14:44,714
血管里有吸血鬼血的游客尸体
and vampire blood in their veins.

263
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,182
难免有意外嘛
有人喝醉失足摔下阳台
It happens. Someone takes
a drunken tumble off a balcony

264
00:14:47,419 --> 00:14:48,545
或掉进密西西比河里
or into the Mississippi.

265
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:51,053
今天就有两具尸体需要处理
And today, I got two
of them to deal with.

266
00:14:53,993 --> 00:14:57,292
打扰一下，亲爱的
你在念什么呢？
Excuse me, love.
What's that you're studying?

267
00:14:57,463 --> 00:14:59,294
变态心理学
Abnormal psychology.

268
00:14:59,465 --> 00:15:00,830
变态心理学
Abnormal psychology.

269
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:05,232
或许你可以帮我这位朋友诊断一下
Well, perhaps you can help me
diagnose my friend over here.

270
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,032
他最近有点情绪低落
He's been a little bit depressed.

271
00:15:08,207 --> 00:15:10,334
老是在想一个女孩
Can't keep his mind off a girl.

272
00:15:10,509 --> 00:15:13,478
他跟我说那女孩是配得上国王的王后
He tells me she's a queen,
fit for a king.

273
00:15:15,547 --> 00:15:17,606
我认为他应该放手向前看
I think he should cut
his losses and move on.

274
00:15:17,783 --> 00:15:19,614
你有什么专业意见？
What's your professional opinion?

275
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:24,988
做一个好人，或许机会
Be a nice guy,
and maybe the opportunity

276
00:15:25,157 --> 00:15:26,522
就会找上门来
will present itself someday.

277
00:15:27,493 --> 00:15:30,792
今晚怎么样？九点？
How about tonight?
Nine o'clock?

278
00:15:30,963 --> 00:15:32,487
我就在这里等你
I'll meet you, right here?

279
00:15:33,866 --> 00:15:35,527
我会考虑的
I'll take it under consideration.

280
00:15:38,437 --> 00:15:39,995
强硬
Hm. Harsh.

281
00:15:40,539 --> 00:15:42,734
看来我魅力不再了
I dare say, I've lost my touch.

282
00:15:42,908 --> 00:15:44,876
或是你魅力不再了
Or you've lost yours.

283
00:15:48,847 --> 00:15:49,939
等等
Oh, hey, hey.

284
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:51,241
打烊了，抱歉
We're closed, sorry.

285
00:15:51,417 --> 00:15:54,250
我只需要一点点草药
拜托
I just need one teeny, tiny,
little herb. Please?

286
00:15:54,887 --> 00:15:56,252
什么草药？
Which herb?

287
00:15:56,422 --> 00:15:57,821
研磨好的附子花
Crushed aconite flower.

288
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:00,488
附子草？那可是毒药
Wolf's-bane?
That's a poison.

289
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:02,558
想要杀死哪个狼人吗？
Looking to kill a wolf?

290
00:16:03,696 --> 00:16:05,391
只是一只小狼
Just a little one.

291
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,195
等我一下
Gimme a minute.

292
00:16:19,411 --> 00:16:22,278
和曼陀罗混在一起，滴几滴在热茶里
Cut it with Jimson weed....
A few drops in some hot tea.

293
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:23,915
这样就行了
That should do it.

294
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:25,345
给你
Here.

295
00:16:25,517 --> 00:16:26,984
狼人要在这城市生存很难
It's an ugly town for wolves.

296
00:16:28,387 --> 00:16:30,048
你这么做是对的
You're doing the right thing.

297
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:42,224
嘿，想讨赏吗？
Hey, wanna gain points?

298
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:45,728
告诉马赛尔法语区有个狼人
Tell Marcel there's a werewolf
in the Quarter.

299
00:16:46,972 --> 00:16:49,202
你带我来了个绝佳之地
KLAUS: You take me
to the nicest places.

300
00:16:52,878 --> 00:16:54,846
欢迎来到死后的世界
Welcome to the land
of the newly-dead.

301
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,379
我就不浪费时间了
I won't waste your time.

302
00:16:56,548 --> 00:16:58,243
我想你跟他们说明过情况了
I trust you filled them in.

303
00:16:58,417 --> 00:17:00,647
说实话，这两个没什么潜力
To be honest, not much
in the way of potential here.

304
00:17:00,819 --> 00:17:03,515
是吗？我刚失去六个夜行者
Yeah, well,
I just lost six Nightwalkers.

305
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:05,122
我得填补空缺
I got holes to fill.

306
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:07,622
我速战速决
你们感到渴望
I'll keep this quick.
That itch you feel?

307
00:17:07,793 --> 00:17:09,727
是吸血的需求越加强烈
That's the need to feed
coming on strong.

308
00:17:09,895 --> 00:17:11,294
渴望吸食人血
A hunger for human blood.

309
00:17:11,463 --> 00:17:14,660
你就成为吸血鬼
你就会再死一次
Drink it, you're a vampire,
don't, you die. Again.

310
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:17,893
这次是永久的，死在这运尸袋里
This time, for good.
Right here, in a body-bag.

311
00:17:18,070 --> 00:17:20,595
你想留下谁？
漂亮傻女孩还是同志好友？
Hey, what do you think?
Cute, dorky girl or gay best friend?

312
00:17:20,773 --> 00:17:22,240
你来选吧
Dealer's choice.

313
00:17:22,408 --> 00:17:24,137
我来选，好吧
Dealer's choice, okay.

314
00:17:24,309 --> 00:17:27,642
捡到这枚硬币的人得永生
Whoever picks up this coin
gets to live forever.

315
00:17:29,281 --> 00:17:30,578
另一个人就得死
The other one dies.

316
00:17:33,452 --> 00:17:34,919
开始
Go.

317
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:40,187
该死，女孩，真该死
(LAUGHS)
Damn, girl! I said, damn!

318
00:17:40,359 --> 00:17:41,451
你怎么能这样？
How could you?

319
00:17:41,627 --> 00:17:43,527
好了，乔许，我别无选择
Get over it, Josh.
It's not like I had a choice.

320
00:17:43,695 --> 00:17:46,391
你也会这么做的
但你是个软弱的小…
You would've done the same thing,
but you're such a little weak--

321
00:17:51,770 --> 00:17:53,499
让她在坟墓里自生自灭吧
Let her die in cold storage.

322
00:17:54,306 --> 00:17:57,139
背叛朋友就是这个下场
Got a thing about people
who betray their own friends.

323
00:17:57,810 --> 00:18:00,438
走吧，我们去兜个风
Come on.
Let's go for a ride.

324
00:18:02,014 --> 00:18:03,504
走吧
Go.

325
00:18:11,857 --> 00:18:13,415
好，就这样
All right.
That's it.

326
00:18:19,431 --> 00:18:21,126
让我看看你还有什么本事
Tell me what else you've got.

327
00:18:31,643 --> 00:18:33,873
触剑攻击，换反防守
Attaque au fer!
Now, counter-parry.

328
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:36,845
击中，明显击中了
A hit!
Palpable hit.

329
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:41,715
有朝一日我要娶你
I'm gonna marry you, someday.

330
00:18:41,887 --> 00:18:44,651
我才不会嫁个决斗时打不过我的人
I would never marry someone
who couldn't best me in a duel.

331
00:18:46,091 --> 00:18:47,558
再来一局吗？
Another lesson?

332
00:19:27,399 --> 00:19:28,661
蕾贝卡米卡森
Rebekah Mikaelson.

333
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:32,436
又来教我击剑了吗？
Come to teach me another lesson?

334
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:40,842
我上次见你时，皇家卫起火了
